ANC Stalwart and a vocal critic of Former President Jacob Zuma, Reverand Frank Chikane, is appearing before the State Capture Inquiry today. Chikane served as Director general in the Presidency under Thabo Mbeki, and has previously said state capture was an act of treason. JOHANNESBURG - The state capture inquiry heard testimony from ANC stalwart Reverend Frank Chikane. The commission also heard testimony from Acting Head of Directorate for Priority Crime Investigation (Hawks) Lieutenant Yolisa Matakata. WATCH: Lord Peter Hain says global banks complicit in state capture On Monday, former British MP Lord Peter Hain testified at the commission. He told the Zondo commission that the country has adequate laws but their enforcement is weak.